---
import ServiceCityPage from '~/components/pages/ServiceCityPage.astro';
import { services, cities } from '~/data/service-city-config';
---

<ServiceCityPage service={services['ev-chargers']} city={cities['holland-mi']}>
  <section class="container section-pad">
    <h2>Holland BPW $1,000 Rebate — When You Bundle EV Charger + Panel Upgrade</h2>
    <p>
      Holland BPW pays a <strong>$1,000 rebate</strong> when a residential panel upgrade to 200 amps is paired with a qualifying
      EV charger installed within 12 months. If you're installing an EV charger and your existing panel is at or below 150
      amps, upgrading to 200 amps at the same time captures both the rebate and the headroom your electrical system needs
      anyway.
    </p>
    <p><strong>The combination that qualifies:</strong></p>
    <ul>
      <li>Holland BPW electric service (check your utility bill).</li>
      <li>Panel upgrade to at least 200 amps.</li>
      <li>Level 2 EV charger installed (NEMA 14-50 outlet or hardwired) within 12 months.</li>
      <li>Licensed electrician with closed electrical permit.</li>
      <li>Pre-approval recommended — call BPW at 616-355-1577 before starting.</li>
    </ul>
    <p>
      You can also stack this with the federal IRA tax credit (30% up to $1,000 for the EV charger), Consumers Energy or
      DTE rebates if you're outside BPW territory, or manufacturer rebates on specific Tesla, ChargePoint, or Wallbox
      models. See our <a href="/blog/holland-bpw-panel-rebate-guide">full Holland BPW rebate guide</a> for documentation
      and the application process.
    </p>
  </section>
</ServiceCityPage>
